@startuml
title OCI Queue Reconcile Model

[*] --> Ready : ACTIVE
[*] --> Retryable : CREATING / UPDATING / DELETING
[*] --> Failed : FAILED / DELETED

Ready : secret present
Retryable : requeue required

Ready --> Ready : supported drift update\n(displayName, visibility, timeout,\nDLQ count, tags, custom key)
Ready --> Retryable : OCI enters nonterminal state
Retryable --> Ready : lifecycle becomes ACTIVE
Retryable --> Failed : lifecycle becomes FAILED or DELETED
Ready --> Deleting : delete requested
Retryable --> Deleting : delete requested
Failed --> Deleting : delete requested
Deleting --> Deleted : resource gone, finalizer removed

note right of Ready
  retentionInSeconds drift returns a reconcile error
  and blocks compartment moves and UpdateQueue.
  Empty customEncryptionKeyId is treated as no-op.
end note

@enduml
